PROJECT NAME: Trading AI (Android App)

TECH STACK:
- Java (Android SDK)
- Firebase (Authentication + Firestore)
- Material Design 3
- Web3 Integration (MetaMask via deep link or WalletConnect)
- MVVM architecture

APP PURPOSE:
This app is a gateway ecosystem for the Trading AI Windows bot.
It does NOT execute trades.
It provides access, investment options, education, and affiliate system.

MAIN FEATURES:

1) AUTHENTICATION
- Firebase Email/Password login
- Google Sign-In
- Store user data in Firestore:
  userId
  email
  walletAddress
  affiliateCode
  referredBy
  role (user/admin)

2) HOME DASHBOARD (4 BUTTONS)
- Use Windows Version
- Invest via Web3
- Education
- Affiliate Program

3) WINDOWS VERSION SECTION
- Description of Windows Trading AI
- Download button (external link)
- Installation guide
- FAQ section
- No trading logic inside Android app

4) WEB3 INVESTMENT SECTION
- Connect MetaMask (deep link or WalletConnect)
- Show connected wallet address
- Invest button → triggers smart contract transaction
- Track transaction hash
- Show investment history
- Show status (Pending / Confirmed / Claimed)
- Do NOT store private keys
- All signing must happen inside wallet

5) EDUCATION SECTION
- Course list
- Course detail page
- Paid course option
- Enrollment system
- Track user progress
- Unlock content after payment

6) AFFILIATE SYSTEM
- Generate unique referral code per user
- Track referred users in Firestore
- Track commission %
- Dashboard:
  - Total referrals
  - Active investors
  - Commission earned
  - Withdraw option

7) ADMIN ROLE
- View total users
- View total investments
- Manage courses
- Manage affiliate settings
- Enable/Disable investment

SECURITY REQUIREMENTS:
- Firebase security rules
- No private key storage
- Input validation
- Secure API keys
- Prevent duplicate investment submission

UI REQUIREMENTS:
- Clean modern UI
- Dark mode support
- Loading states
- Error handling
- Proper navigation (BottomNavigation or Drawer)

DELIVERABLES:
- Full Android project structure
- Firebase setup guide
- Web3 integration template
- Firestore database structure
- Sample security rules
- Required Gradle dependencies

IMPORTANT:
- Show clear risk disclaimer
- No guaranteed profit claims
- Transparent user communication
